<p>The <b>turnip</b> or <b>white turnip</b> (<i><a href="/wiki/Brassica_rapa" title="Brassica rapa">Brassica rapa</a></i> var. <i>rapa</i>) is a <a href="/wiki/Root_vegetable" title="Root vegetable" class="mw-redirect">root vegetable</a> commonly grown in <a href="/wiki/Temperate_climate" title="Temperate climate" class="mw-redirect">temperate climates</a> worldwide for its white, bulbous <a href="/wiki/Taproot" title="Taproot">taproot</a>. Small, tender varieties are grown for human consumption, while larger varieties are grown as <a href="/wiki/Fodder" title="Fodder">feed</a> for <a href="/wiki/Livestock" title="Livestock">livestock</a>.</p>
